body:
It&#039;s hilarious though. It kinda makes me think that Zilean has turned into somewhat of a mini game of &quot;Ah Hah! I hit the adc!&quot; 

Then, the more I think about this change the more I see the changes with ALL support champions that are similar to him. Obviously there are the tanky supports that are prepared to set up engages and all-ins (blitz, thresh, leona, braum, etc) And then there are the Harrassing/Utility  Supports (lulu, zilean, karma, sona, soraka, etc) 

The harassing supports have all been slowly changing into low damage, minimal CC, mild sustain, meandering ward bots with little to no real impact on the game other than vision. The very few exceptions to this rule are Morgana and maybe lux. Morgana can cheese Q&#039;s all day and as long as one hits you can expect to take a lot of damage. land karma&#039;s ulted Q? nice, but they&#039;ll heal it back
